methods.getVariableNames:
Retrieves all of the variable names present in the session's scope

:return: (java.util.Set<java.lang.String>) an unmodifiable set of variable names
methods.getVariables:
Retrieves all of the variables present in the session's scope (e.g., Groovy binding, Python globals()).

:return: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>) an unmodifiable map with variable names as the keys, and the Objects as the result

methods.initializeTransientFieldsForLiveness:
Package-private for Serializable sub-classes to use in readObject only.
 Public to allow unit tests in another package to work around mock issues where the constructor is never invoked.
methods.isValidImportString:
Ensure that the given importString is valid. Return a canonical version of the import string if it is valid.

:param log: io.deephaven.io.logger.Logger
:param importString: (java.lang.String) - the string to check. importString is "[import] [static]
        package.class[.innerclass...][.field|.method][.*][;]".
:return: (java.lang.String) null if importString is not valid, else a string of the form "import [static]
         package.class.part.part[.*];"

methods.removeComments:
Remove comments from an import statement. /* comments take precedence over eol (//) comments. This ignores
 escaping and quoting, as they are not valid in an import statement.

:param s: (java.lang.String) - import statement string from which to remove comments
:return: (java.lang.String) the input string with comments removed, and whitespace trimmed
methods.sanitizeThrowable:
If this script session can throw unserializable exceptions, this method is responsible for turning those
 exceptions into something suitable for sending back to a client.

:return: (java.lang.Throwable) the sanitized exception

If this referent is "live", behave as LivenessReferent.retainReference() and return true. Otherwise, returns false rather
